02/03/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The Socialist Party's (SP) return to parliament after a six-month boycott is the first step towards normalising parliamentary work, the President of the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe (PACE), Mevlut Cavusoglu, said in a statement Monday (March 1st). Cavusoglu described contributions by all parties as essential, adding that parliamentary dialogue is crucial to the democratic functioning of state institutions, as well as reforms. (Lajmifundit, Klan, Shekulli, Top Channel, Balkan Web, Alsat - 01/03/10)
